"In geometry, the nonconvex great rhombicosidodecahedron is a nonconvex uniform polyhedron, indexed as U. It is also called the quasirhombicosidodecahedron. It is given a Schlfli symbol t{5/3,3}. Its vertex figure is a crossed quadrilateral."
"This model shares the name with the convex ""great rhombicosidodecahedron"", also known as the truncated icosidodecahedron."
